# Unfixed glibc (libc6) CVEs in the gcr.io/distroless/cc-debian12 base image.
# Debian has classified all four `<no-dsa>` ("Minor issue") for bookworm —
# no security-advisory fix is planned, so no base-image update resolves them:
#   https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-6238
#   https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-5928
#   https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-5450
#   https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-5435
# All four affect deprecated debugging-only resolver functions
# (ns_printrrf/ns_printrr/fp_nquery) or scanf/%mc and ungetwc edge cases this
# workspace's binaries do not exercise. `exp:` forces a revisit rather than
# relying on someone rereading this comment — re-check the Debian tracker
# links above when the gate reactivates on expiry.
CVE-2026-6238 exp:2027-01-02
CVE-2026-5928 exp:2027-01-02
CVE-2026-5450 exp:2027-01-02
CVE-2026-5435 exp:2027-01-02
